      • messageProcessTransaction

        default ClusterStatsCollector.Transaction messageProcessTransaction(Object message)

      • messageDispatched

        void messageDispatched(Object message)
        Container calls this method before invoking an MP's MessageHandler or Output method. A message processing "transaction" opens with a messageDispatched. It the closes with one of the following:
        • messageProcessed - successfully handled
        • messageFailed - there was an error

      • messageProcessed

        void messageProcessed(Object message)
        Container calls this method when successfully invoking an MP's MessageHandler or Output method.

      • messageFailed

        void messageFailed(boolean mpFailure)
        Container calls this method when invoking an MP's MessageHandler or Output method results in an error.

      • messageCollision

        void messageCollision(Object message)
        The dispatcher calls this method in its onMessage handler when it discards a message due to a collision at the Mp. This number will ALSO be reflected in the messageDiscarded results.

      • messageProcessorCreated

        void messageProcessorCreated(Object key)
